        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

            <!-- Our Commitment -->
            <div class="accessibility-section">
                <h2>Our Accessibility Commitment</h2>
                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <p><strong>Village Pediatrics is committed to ensuring that our website is accessible to all users, including individuals with disabilities.</strong> We believe that everyone should have equal access to information and functionality on our website.</p>
                </div>
                <p>We are continuously working to improve the accessibility and usability of our website to ensure we provide equal access to information and functionality for all our users. This commitment extends to our online services, patient portal, and all digital communications.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Standards and Guidelines -->
            <div class="accessibility-section">
                <h2>Accessibility Standards</h2>

                <h3>WCAG 2.1 Compliance</h3>
                <p>Our website aims to conform with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards. These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible for people with disabilities and create a better user experience for everyone.</p>

                <h3>ADA Compliance</h3>
                <p>We strive to ensure our website complies with the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) by:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Providing alternative text for images and graphics</li>
                    <li>Ensuring proper color contrast ratios</li>
                    <li>Making all content accessible via keyboard navigation</li>
                    <li>Using semantic HTML structure and proper headings</li>
                    <li>Providing clear and consistent navigation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Accessibility Features -->
            <div class="accessibility-section">
                <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>

                <div class="feature-box">
                    <h3>Current Accessibility Features</h3>
                    <p>Our website includes the following accessibility features:</p>
                </div>

                <h3>Keyboard Navigation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>All interactive elements are accessible via keyboard</li>
                    <li>Logical tab order throughout the website</li>
                    <li>Visible focus indicators for keyboard users</li>
                    <li>Skip navigation links for screen reader users</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Screen Reader Support</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Semantic HTML markup for proper content structure</li>
                    <li>Descriptive headings organized in a logical hierarchy</li>
                    <li>Alternative text for all meaningful images</li>
                    <li>ARIA labels and descriptions where appropriate</li>
                    <li>Form labels clearly associated with input fields</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Visual Accessibility</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>High contrast color schemes for better readability</li>
                    <li>Readable fonts and appropriate font sizes</li>
                    <li>Scalable text that can be enlarged up to 200% without loss of functionality</li>
                    <li>Support for high contrast mode preferences</li>
                    <li>Clear visual hierarchy and spacing</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Motor Accessibility</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Large, easily clickable buttons and links</li>
                    <li>Sufficient spacing between interactive elements</li>
                    <li>Support for reduced motion preferences</li>
                    <li>Alternative input methods supported</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Assistive Technologies -->
            <div class="accessibility-section">
                <h2>Supported Assistive Technologies</h2>
                <p>Our website is designed to be compatible with various assistive technologies, including:</p>

                <h3>Screen Readers</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>JAWS (Job Access With Speech)</li>
                    <li>NVDA (NonVisual Desktop Access)</li>
                    <li>VoiceOver (macOS and iOS)</li>
                    <li>TalkBack (Android)</li>
                    <li>Dragon NaturallySpeaking</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Browser Features</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Browser zoom functionality (up to 200%)</li>
                    <li>High contrast mode</li>
                    <li>Reduced motion settings</li>
                    <li>Font size adjustments</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Mobile Accessibility</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Mobile screen reader compatibility</li>
                    <li>Touch target sizing for motor accessibility</li>
                    <li>Responsive design for various screen sizes</li>
                    <li>Voice control support</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Known Limitations -->
            <div class="accessibility-section">
                <h2>Known Limitations and Ongoing Improvements</h2>

                <h3>Areas of Ongoing Improvement</h3>
                <p>We are continuously working to enhance our website's accessibility. Current areas of focus include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Enhancing video content with captions and transcripts</li>
                    <li>Improving form error messaging and validation</li>
                    <li>Optimizing complex interactive elements</li>
                    <li>Regular accessibility audits and testing</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Third-Party Content</h3>
                <p>Some third-party content and services on our website may not fully meet our accessibility standards. We are working with our vendors to improve accessibility of:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Online appointment scheduling systems</li>
                    <li>Patient portal functionality</li>
                    <li>Payment processing interfaces</li>
                    <li>Social media integrations</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Alternative Access Methods -->
            <div class="accessibility-section">
                <h2>Alternative Access Methods</h2>

                <h3>Phone and In-Person Services</h3>
                <p>If you encounter barriers on our website or need information in an alternative format, we offer these options:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Phone Support:</strong> Call us at (904) 940-1577 during business hours</li>
